<subSubSection pageId="47" pageNumber="48" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="47.[151,1436,229,676]" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,544,338,364]" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">Distribution and ecology:—</emphasis>
<collectingCountry box="[544,675,338,364]" name="Costa Rica" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">Costa Rica</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[686,810,338,364]" name="Venezuela" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">Venezuela</collectingCountry>
, and 
<collectingCountry box="[871,975,338,364]" name="Trinidad and Tobago" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">Trinidad</collectingCountry>
; likely to be more widespread. It grows on open banks at forest edges or along roadsides, forming mixed colonies with 
<taxonomicName authorityName="J. Gonzales" authorityYear="2011" baseAuthorityName="Jermy &amp; T. G. Walker" baseAuthorityYear="2011" box="[1076,1229,377,402]" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Gleicheniaceae" genus="Sticherus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gleicheniales" pageId="47" pageNumber="48" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="interjectus">
<emphasis box="[1076,1229,377,402]" italics="true" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">S. interjectus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Chrysler" authorityYear="1944" baseAuthorityName="Kaulf." box="[1285,1407,377,402]" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Gleicheniaceae" genus="Sticherus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gleicheniales" pageId="47" pageNumber="48" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="remotus">
<emphasis box="[1285,1407,377,402]" italics="true" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">S. remotus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
at 
<quantity box="[151,272,416,442]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.3" metricValueMax="6.0" metricValueMin="0.6" pageId="47" pageNumber="48" unit="m" value="330.0" valueMax="600.0" valueMin="60.0">
60– 
<specimenCount box="[195,272,416,442]" pageId="47" pageNumber="48" type="generic">600 m</specimenCount>
</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="47.[151,1436,229,676]" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,307,454,480]" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">Notes:—</emphasis>
This hybrid between 
<taxonomicName authorityName="J. Gonzales" authorityYear="2011" baseAuthorityName="Jermy &amp; T. G. Walker" baseAuthorityYear="2011" box="[564,720,455,480]" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Gleicheniaceae" genus="Sticherus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gleicheniales" pageId="47" pageNumber="48" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="interjectus">
<emphasis box="[564,720,455,480]" italics="true" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">S. interjectus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Chrysler" authorityYear="1944" baseAuthorityName="Kaulf." box="[782,907,455,480]" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Gleicheniaceae" genus="Sticherus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gleicheniales" pageId="47" pageNumber="48" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="remotus">
<emphasis box="[782,907,455,480]" italics="true" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">S. remotus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was cytologically studied and described by 
<bibRefCitation author="Jermy, A. C. &amp; Walker, T. G." box="[151,463,493,519]" pageId="47" pageNumber="48" pagination="258 - 264" refId="ref31812" refString="Jermy, A. C. &amp; Walker, T. G. (1985) Cytotaxonomic studies of the ferns of Trinidad. Bulletin of the British Museum Natural History Botany 13: 185 - 191, 258 - 264." type="journal article" year="1985">Jermy and Walker (1985)</bibRefCitation>
. It differs from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="J. Gonzales" authorityYear="2011" baseAuthorityName="Jermy &amp; T. G. Walker" baseAuthorityYear="2011" box="[657,815,493,518]" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Gleicheniaceae" genus="Sticherus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gleicheniales" pageId="47" pageNumber="48" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="interjectus">
<emphasis box="[657,815,493,518]" italics="true" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">S. interjectus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the more rounded and broader bases of the bud scales, from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Chrysler" authorityYear="1944" baseAuthorityName="Kaulf." box="[300,422,532,557]" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Gleicheniaceae" genus="Sticherus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gleicheniales" pageId="47" pageNumber="48" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="remotus">
<emphasis box="[300,422,532,557]" italics="true" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">S. remotus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the approximate segments, abaxial segment surfaces scales, and it is different from both these species by having less regularly shaped and darkened scale cells. Many species in the species complex around 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Chrysler" authorityYear="1944" baseAuthorityName="Kaulf." box="[349,472,612,637]" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Gleicheniaceae" genus="Sticherus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gleicheniales" pageId="47" pageNumber="48" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="remotus">
<emphasis box="[349,472,612,637]" italics="true" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">S. remotus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
have unequally developed 2 
<superScript attach="left" box="[811,827,609,623]" fontSize="6" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">nd</superScript>
branches, and this pattern is particularly noticeable in 
<emphasis box="[181,371,651,676]" italics="true" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">S. × subremotus</emphasis>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
